Core Responsibilities
Balance Monitoring

The module should continuously track balances for all registered wallets.

It should identify:

Current token balances
Native chain balances
USD value per asset
Allocation by wallet
Allocation by chain
Total treasury value
Transaction Monitoring

The module should track all relevant wallet transactions.

It should identify:

Inflows
Outflows
Internal transfers
Large movements
Unknown counterparties
Repeated transaction patterns
Unexpected token movements
Wallet Classification

Each wallet should be classified based on its treasury function.

Example categories:

Operating
Reserve
Yield
Multisig
Execution
Governance
Unknown

This classification helps the Portfolio Manager understand how funds are distributed across the treasury structure.

Abnormal Activity Detection

The Wallets module should flag unusual behavior.

Examples:

Large unexpected outflow
Transfer to unknown counterparty
Rapid balance decrease
New token received from unknown source
Unusual transaction frequency
Wallet balance below minimum threshold

Example alert:

{
  "alert_type": "large_outflow",
  "wallet_id": "wallet_001",
  "severity": "high",
  "message": "Large USDC outflow detected from reserve wallet.",
  "tx_hash": "0xabc123"
}
Integration With Portfolio Manager

The Wallets module sends normalized wallet data to the Portfolio Manager.

The Portfolio Manager uses this data to:

Calculate total treasury value
Analyze asset allocation
Compare current allocation against treasury policy
Identify rebalancing opportunities
Generate treasury reports
Integration With Risk Engine

The Risk Engine uses wallet data to evaluate:

Asset concentration risk
Chain concentration risk
Stablecoin exposure
Counterparty exposure
Liquidity risk
Operational wallet risk
Security Principles

The Wallets module should follow strict security boundaries:

Read-only wallet access by default
No private keys stored
No seed phrases stored
No automatic transaction signing
No direct fund control
Multisig-first design
Human approval required for execution
Full logging of wallet monitoring events
Example Workflow
A treasury wallet is added to the system.
The Wallets module detects the chain and address type.
Token balances are fetched.
Recent transactions are analyzed.
Wallet data is normalized.
The Portfolio Manager receives updated balance data.
The Risk Engine evaluates wallet-related risks.
Alerts are generated if abnormal activity is detected.
